{"original text":"File documents an unsuccessful competition entry for a bridge design to be used in Leidschenveen, a planned residential area of The Hague, Netherlands. The design was to be used as a standard design for 60 different bridges, including general traffic bridges, bicycle and pedestrian bridges, and pedestrian-only bridges. Whether or not the competition entry was ever completed or submitted cannot be determined from the content of the file. This file also includes design development drawings, possibly for a gallery or exhibition space. Material in this file was produced between 1997 and 1998, but predominantly in 1997.\nGroup DR2004:0335 in this file contains a map which is possibly related to Halmag (AP144.S2.D178).","processed_text":"File documents an unsuccessful competition entry for a bridge design to be used in Leidschenveen, a planned residential area of The Hague, Netherlands. The design was to be used as a standard design for 60 different bridges, including general traffic bridges, bicycle and pedestrian bridges, and pedestrian-only bridges. Whether or not the competition entry was ever completed or submitted cannot be determined from the content of the file. This file also includes design development drawings, possibly for a gallery or exhibition space. Material in this file was produced between 1997 and 1998, but predominantly in 1997.\nGroup  in this file contains a map which is possibly related to Halmag (AP144.S2.D178)."}
